Prepare Carnation(R) Simple White Sauce by melting butter in medium saucepan, add flour and cook over low heat stirring for 1 minute. Whisk in milk and salt. Bring to a boil, lower heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until sauce has thickened. Add Parmesan cheese, stirring until melted. Stir in chicken stock. Cook bacon or pancetta in a skillet, until crisp, about 2-3 minutes. Add to white sauce and stir until combined.